'''''Desulfurobacterium thermolithotrophum''''' is a species of [[autotrophic]], [[sulphur]]-reducing bacterium isolated from a deep-sea [[hydrothermal vent]]. It is the type species of its genus, being [[thermophilic]], anaerobic, [[Gram-negative]], [[motile]] and rod-shaped, with type strain BSA<sup>T</sup> (= DSM 11699<sup>T</sup>).<ref name="L'HaridonCilia1998">{{cite journal|last1=L'Haridon|first1=S.|last2=Cilia|first2=V.|last3=Messner|first3=P.|last4=Raguenes|first4=G.|last5=Gambacorta|first5=A.|last6=Sleytr|first6=U. B.|last7=Prieur|first7=D.|last8=Jeanthon|first8=C.|title=Desulfurobacterium thermolithotrophum gen. nov., sp. nov., a novel autotrophic, sulphur-reducing bacterium isolated from a deep-sea hydrothermal vent|journal=International Journal of Systematic Bacteriology|volume=48|issue=3|year=1998|pages=701–711|issn=0020-7713|doi=10.1099/00207713-48-3-701|pmid=9734024}}</ref>

