{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}} {{Use Australian English|date=February 2014}} '''Frank D. Fletcher''' was a sailor, mainly known for his time as Chief Officer of the [[SY Aurora|SY ''Aurora'']] during the 1911-1914 [[Australasian Antarctic Expedition]], under Captain [[John King Davis]].<ref name="Bio">{{cite web |url= http://www.mawsonshuts.aq/voyages/people-of-aurora/f.d.fletcher.html |title= People of Aurora: F. D. Fletcher |work= Mawson's Huts Foundation |publisher= [[Australian Antarctic Division]] |accessdate= 2011-03-19}}</ref><ref name="Crew">{{cite web |url= http://www.mawsonshuts.aq/voyages/people-of-aurora/crewmen-of-aurora.html |title= People of Aurora: The men of ''Aurora'' |work= Mawson's Huts Foundation |publisher= [[Australian Antarctic Division]] |accessdate= 2011-03-19}}</ref> Fletcher replaced N. C. Toutcher—who had been Chief Officer during ''Aurora''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s first voyage of the expedition—for the second Antarctic voyage, and the spring and winter sub-Antarctic voyages of 1912 and 1913.<ref name="Bio"/><ref name="Davis p. 170">{{Citation |author= Davis, John King|title= With the "Aurora" in the Antarctic, 1911-1914|origyear=|year=1919|publisher=A. Melrose |location=London |isbn=|page=170}}</ref> In his 1962 book ''High latitude'', Davis described Fletcher as "a most efficient and conscientious officer and seaman who at first sight might have been taken for the prototype of the perfect 'Bucko', that semi-legendary figure sometimes described as having 'a jaw like a sea boot'."<ref name="Davis p. 170"/> Fletcher left the ''Aurora'' in 1913 to join a coastal shipping company, presumably in New Zealand, where he was discharged.<ref name="Crew"/><ref name="Blair bio">{{cite web |url = http://www.mawsonshuts.aq/voyages/people-of-aurora/john-h-blair.html |title = People of Aurora: John H. Blair |work = Mawson's Huts Foundation |publisher = [[Australian Antarctic Division]] |accessdate = 2011-03-21 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110531183813/http://www.mawsonshuts.aq/voyages/people-of-aurora/john-h-blair.html |archivedate = 31 May 2011 |df = dmy-all }}</ref>
Expedition Commander [[Douglas Mawson]] named [[Fletcher Island]], near [[Commonwealth Bay]] in Antarctica, after him.<ref name="AADC">{{cite web |url= http://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=1036 |title= Fletcher Island |work= Australian Antarctic Data Centre |publisher= [[Australian Antarctic Division]] |accessdate= 2011-03-19}}</ref>
