{{Unreferenced|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox book | name = The Pleasure of Finding Things Out | orig title = | translator = | image = The pleasure of finding things out.jpg | caption = 1999 hardcover edition | author = [[Carl Feynman]], [[Michelle Feynman]] | cover_artist = Bruce W. Bond | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Biography]] | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[Perseus Books]] (USA) | release_date = July, 1999 (USA) | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 270 pp | isbn = 0-7382-0108-1 | dewey= 500 21 | congress= Q171 .F385 1999 | oclc= 42564066 }} {{wikiquote|Richard Feynman}} '''''The Pleasure of Finding Things Out''''' is a collection of short works from American [[physicist]] [[Richard Feynman]], including interviews, speeches, lectures, and printed articles. Among these is his famous 1959 lecture "[[There's Plenty of Room at the Bottom]]", his report on the [[Space Shuttle Challenger disaster|Space Shuttle ''Challenger'' disaster]], and his speech on scientific integrity in which he coined the term "[[cargo cult science]]". The original foreword was written by [[Freeman Dyson]].
